snippet.textDisplay:
Thing is... I remember watching Andy Tate's videos after the City and Liverpool defeats 6 years ago. They may have gone viral and people outside of the club may have laughed, but I felt every single word. I remember at the time thinking things couldn't/wouldn't get much worse, that the club had just had the shock of its life, and that there would be a managerial change and significant and sensible footballing investment that summer...


If you told me then that 6 years later Andy Tate would be appearing after another City belting, saying similar things, and that there had been significant but substantially stupid investment, and that things were arguably worse than they were then; there's not a chance in the world I'd believe it.


My heart hurts at this point, football isn't fun anymore, and I feel pure desperation at this point watching Liverpool and City make great appointment after great appointment. We're so far away it hurts, I'm sick of seeing old timer United supporters give it the "ahhh pipe down it was worse in the 70's" gambit... Why does that matter? Why is that relevant? We haven't won a leave in 6 years. That'll soon be 10. Before we know it it'll be 15 and then 30...

snippet.textDisplay:
How has Ole earned his time? Week after week of clear non existent or ineffectual coaching and it shows. When was the last worked set piece United have had since Ole signed? Which player has improved under his coaching methods? When was the last time you could explain United's pattern of play or gameplan to anyone? When was the last time you could confidently back United to win? When was the last time managers at United were held to high standards and expectations? When was the last time you saw a logical team selection from Ole? When was the last time you heard United get linked to a big name because of the manager? When was the last time a manager could be hired on sentiment?

Out of his depth, out of his mind.

Saying no manager would be able to coach these players better is actually an insult to Ole because it clearly shows his ineptitude as a coach. Saying he can do better he just needs time is the same thing we used to make fun of Arsenal fans for when they backed Wenger. Saying that counterattacking is now somehow a complete tactical gameplan means literally any FIFA player with half a brain could be doing Ole's job.

Excuses.
